---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Rhysora"
  description="How Wilrhys Limited (trading as Rhysora) collects, uses, and protects personal data under UK GDPR."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        How we handle the personal data you provide when you contact us or visit
        rhysora.com.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 23 April 2026.</p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Rhysora is a product operated by Wilrhys Limited, a company registered
          in England and Wales (Company No. 15731165), with registered office in
          Stevenage, Hertfordshire. Wilrhys Limited is the data controller for
          any personal data collected via rhysora.com.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contact for data matters: <a href="mailto:info@rhysora.com">info@rhysora.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>What personal data we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We only collect personal data that you provide directly when contacting us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your name and email address (when you email info@rhysora.com)</li>
          <li>Any other information you include in your enquiry — for example, your
          job title, organisation, or project context</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not run analytics software on this website. We do not set tracking
          cookies. We do not use advertising trackers or third-party marketing scripts.
        </p>

        <h2>How we use your data</h2>
        <p>
          We use the information you provide to respond to your enquiry and, where
          relevant, to continue a professional conversation about Rhysora products,
          research collaborations, or other business matters you have raised.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our lawful basis for this processing is <em>legitimate interest</em> under
          UK GDPR Article 6(1)(f) — responding to unsolicited business enquiries.
          You can object to this processing at any time by replying to our message
          asking us to stop.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we share your data with</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal data. We do not share it for marketing purposes.
          We may share information with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our email provider (Namecheap Private Email), which stores and transmits
          messages sent to our inboxes. Namecheap operates under its own privacy policy
          and appropriate international data transfer safeguards.</li>
          <li>Any regulator, law enforcement body, or court that lawfully requires
          disclosure.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
        <p>
          We retain email correspondence for as long as the conversation is active
          and for a reasonable period afterwards for business records (typically up
          to 6 years, consistent with UK statutory retention periods for business
          communications). We delete older correspondence on request, and regularly
          as part of good inbox hygiene.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
        <p>
          This website uses no cookies and no tracking technologies. We do not set
          analytics cookies, marketing cookies, or any other client-side tracking.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your browser may receive standard server logs (IP address, user-agent, page
          requested, timestamp) as part of normal web traffic handled by our hosting
          provider (GitHub Pages). These are not used for profiling or marketing.
        </p>

        <h2>Search Console and search engine indexing</h2>
        <p>
          rhysora.com is registered with Google Search Console so we can monitor how
          our pages appear in Google search results. Search Console provides aggregated
          data about which search queries bring visitors to our site. This aggregated
          data does not identify individual visitors.
        </p>

        <h2>International data transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is hosted on GitHub Pages (servers in the US, operated by
          GitHub, Inc.). Our email is hosted on Namecheap Private Email (UK-based
          infrastructure). When a visitor outside the UK contacts us, their data
          may traverse international networks. Both hosting providers operate under
          appropriate safeguards for international data transfers consistent with
          UK GDPR.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate personal data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal data (subject to our legal obligations)</li>
          <li>Restrict or object to our processing of your personal data</li>
          <li>Receive your personal data in a portable format</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent where consent is the lawful basis (not our usual basis)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:info@rhysora.com">info@rhysora.com</a>.
          We will respond within one month.
        </p>

        <h2>How to complain</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe we have handled your personal data unlawfully, you can
          complain to the UK Information Commissioner's Office (ICO):
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a><br />
          Helpline: 0303 123 1113
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Material changes
          will be reflected here with an updated "Last updated" date. Your continued
          use of the site or continued correspondence with us after changes are
          published indicates acceptance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
